acos won 7\u20130 on aggregate.''\n\n====Group stage====\n{{footballbox collapsible\n|date=23 October 2008\n|time=20:15\n|team1=[[Galatasaray S.K. (football)|Galatasaray]] {{flagicon|TUR}}\n|score=1 &ndash; 0\n|report=[http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/season=2009/matches/round=15285/match=304171/index.html (Report)]\n|team2={{flagicon|GRE}} [[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]]\n|goals1=[[Harry Kewell|Kewell]] {{goal|25}}\n|goals2=\n|stadium=[[Ali Sami Yen Stadium]]\n|location=[[Istanbul]], [[Turkey]]\n|attendance=23,500\n|referee=[[Eduardo Iturralde Gonz\u00e1lez]] ([[Spain]])\n|result=L\n}}\n{{footballbox collapsible\n|date=27 November 2008\n|time=20:45\n|team1=[[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]] {{flagicon|GRE}} \n|score=5 &ndash; 1\n|report=[http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/season=2009/matches/round=15285/match=304202/index.html (Report)]\n|team2={{flagicon|POR}} [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]]\n|goals1=[[Luciano Galletti|Galletti]] {{goal|1}}<br>[[Christos Patsatzoglou|Patsatzoglou]] {{goal|17}}<br>[[Diogo Lu\u00eds Santo|Diogo]] {{goal|24||53}}<br>[[Fernando Belluschi|Belluschi]] {{goal|44}}\n|goals2=[[David Luiz]] {{goal|33}}\n|stadium=[[Karaiskakis Stadium]]\n|location=[[Piraeus]], [[Greece]]\n|attendance=30,185\n|referee=St\u00e9phane Lannoy ([[France]])\n|result=W\n}}\n{{footballbox collapsible \n|date=3 December 2008\n|time=20:45\n|team1=[[FC Metalist Kharkiv|Metalist Kharkiv]] {{flagicon|UKR}} \n|score=1 &ndash; 0\n|report=[http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/season=2009/matches/round=15285/match=304218/report=rp.html (Report)]\n|team2={{flagicon|GRE}} [[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]]\n|goals1=[[Edmar Aparecida|Edmar]] {{goal|88}}\n|goals2=\n|stadium=[[Metalist Stadium]]\n|location=[[Kharkiv]], [[Ukraine]]\n|attendance=25,000\n|referee=William Collum ([[Scotland]])\n|result=L\n}}\n{{footballbox collapsible\n|date=18 December 2008\n|time=20:45\n|team1=[[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]] {{flagicon|GRE}} \n|score=4 &ndash; 0\n|report=[http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/s