n the [[UEFA Champions League]], as they were eliminated in the [[UEFA Champions League 2008\u201309#Third qualifying round|UEFA Champions League third qualifying round]] by [[Anorthosis Famagusta FC|Anorthosis]]. In the beginning of the summertime, Olympiacos unveiled [[Spain|Spanish]] [[Ernesto Valverde]] as their new coach.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/footballeurope/news/kind=2/newsid=702323.html |title=Olympiacos turn to Valverde |publisher=[[UEFA|UEFA.com]] |date=2008-05-28 |accessdate=2008-05-29 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080529124054/http://www.uefa.com/footballeurope/news/kind%3D2/newsid%3D702323.html |archivedate=29 May 2008 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==Squad==\n{{Fs start}}\n{{Fs player|no=1|nat=Greece|name=[[Leonidas Panagopoulos]]|pos=GK}}\n{{Fs player|no=2|nat=Greece|name=[[Christos Patsatzoglou]]|pos=DF}}\n{{Fs player|no=3|nat=France|name=[[Didier Domi]]|pos=DF}}\n{{Fs player|no=4|nat=Brazil|name=[[Leonardo de Jesus Geraldo|Leonardo]]|pos=DF}}\n{{Fs player|no=5|nat=Greece|name=[[Georgios Galitsios]]|pos=DF}}\n{{Fs player|no=6|nat=Greece|name=[[Ieroklis Stoltidis]] ''([[Captain (association football)#Vice-captain|vice-captain]])''|pos=MF}}\n{{Fs player|no=7|nat=Argentina|name=[[Luciano Galletti]]|pos=MF}}\n{{Fs player|no=8|nat=Spain|name=[[\u00d3scar Gonz\u00e1lez Marcos|\u00d3scar]]|pos=FW}}\n{{Fs player|no=9|nat=Serbia|name=[[Darko Kova\u010devi\u0107]]|pos=FW}}\n{{Fs player|no=10|nat=Brazil|name=[[Diogo Lu\u00eds Santo|Diogo]]|pos=FW}}\n{{Fs player|no=11|nat=Serbia|name=[[Predrag \u0110or\u0111evi\u0107]] ''([[Captain (association football)|captain]])''|pos=MF}}\n{{Fs player|no=14|nat=Poland|name=[[Micha\u0142 \u017bew\u0142akow]]|pos=DF}}\n{{Fs player|no=15|nat=Spain|name=[[Ra\u00fal Bravo]]|pos=DF}}\n{{Fs player|no=18|nat=Greece|name=[[Paraskevas Antzas]]|pos=DF}}\n{{Fs player|no=19|nat=Greece|name=[[Konstantinos Mendrinos]]|pos=MF}}\n{{Fs mid}}\n{{Fs player|no=20|nat=Brazil|name=[[Dudu Cearense]]|pos=MF}}\n{{Fs player|n