{"title_page": "Sikar Junction railway station", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date = October 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date = October 2018}}\n{{Infobox station\n| name = Sikar Junction railway station\n| style = Indian railway\n| type = [[List of railway stations in India|Indian Railway Station]]\n| image = \n| image_caption = \n| address = [[National Highway 11]], [[Sikar]], [[Rajasthan]]\n| country = India\n| coordinates = {{coord|27.616760|75.153264|type:railwaystation_region:IN|display=inline}}\n| map_type        = India#India Rajasthan\n| elevation = {{convert|432|m|ft}}\n| owned = [[Indian Railways]]\n| operator = [[Jaipur railway division]]\n| line = \n| platform = 3\n| tracks = 5\n| other = Auto stand\n| structure = Standard (on ground station)\n| depth = \n| levels = \n| parking = yes\n| bicycle = No\n| ADA = \n| status = Functioning\n| code = SIKR\n| zone = [[North Western Railway Zone (India)|North Western Railway]]\n| opened = \n| closed = \n| rebuilt = \n| electrified = No\n| former = \n| mpassengers = \n| passengers = \n| pass_system = \n| pass_year = \n| pass_percent = \n| services = <!-- Only use S-rail/S-line Templates here, without start or end -->\n}}'''Sikar Junction railway station''' is a small railway station in [[Sikar district]], [[Rajasthan]]. The station consists of three platforms.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://indiarailinfo.com/arrivals/sikar-junction-sikr/1255|title=SIKR/Sikar Junction|website=India Rail Info}}</ref> Sikar is connected through a [[broad gauge]] railway line section to Delhi Sarai Rohilla and [[Churu, Rajasthan|Churu]]. The [[Sikar]] -  [[Jaipur]]  section  was closed in November 2015,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/jaipur/Jaipur-Sikar-route-to-close-for-gauge-conversion/articleshow/49787326.cms|title=Jaipur-Sikar route to close for gauge conversion - Times of India|website=The Times of India|access-date=2019-01-30}}</ref> along with the broad gauge line to [[Jhunjhunu]], [[Rewari]] and [[Dehli]].\n\nIn September 2015, [[Railway Minister of India]] [[Suresh Prabhu]] flagged two trains to mark the completion of Rs. 260 crore gauge conversion of the {{convert|122|km|mi}} [[Loharu]]-[[Sikar]] railway line in [[Rajasthan]]. [[Sikar]]. The Fatehpur Shekhawati line of {{convert|50|km|mi}} was flagged on  21 June 2017.<ref>[http://www.business-standard.com/article/government-press-release/suresh-prabhu-inaugurates-gauge-conversion-project-of-loharu-sikar-railway-line-115090100575_1.html Suresh Prabhu Inaugurates Gauge Conversion]</ref>\n\n== Major Trains ==\n* [[Delhi Sarai Rohilla\u2013Sikar Express]]\nAmarpur arawali express\n\n==References==\n<references group=\"\"></references>{{Railway stations in Rajasthan}}<br />{{Rajasthan-railstation-stub}}\n[[Category:Railway junction stations in India]]\n[[Category:Railway stations in Sikar district]]\n[[Category:Jaipur railway division]]\n<br />\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date = October 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date = October 2018}}\n{{Infobox station\n| name = Sikar Junction railway station\n| style = Indian railway\n| type = [[List of railway stations in India|Indian Railway Station]]\n| image = \n| image_caption = \n| address = [[National Highway 11]], [[Sikar]], [[Rajasthan]]\n| country = India\n| coordinates = {{coord|27.616760|75.153264|type:railwaystation_region:IN|display=inline}}\n| map_type        = India#India Rajasthan\n| elevation = {{convert|432|m|ft}}\n| owned = [[Indian Railways]]\n| operator = [[Jaipur railway division]]\n| line = \n| platform = 3\n| tracks = 5\n| other = Auto stand\n| structure = Standard (on ground station)\n| depth = \n| levels = \n| parking = yes\n| bicycle = No\n| ADA = \n| status = Functioning\n| code = SIKR\n| zone = [[North Western Railway Zone (India)|North Western Railway]]\n| opened = \n| closed = \n| rebuilt = \n| electrified = No\n| former = \n| mpassengers = \n| passengers = \n| pass_system = \n| pass_year = \n| pass_percent = \n| services = <!-- Only use S-r